    "Sentences\"are composed of these \"words\" (Ofer et al., 2021).",
    "Compared with the traditional natural language processing problem, the protein sequence composed of 20 amino acids is closer to the character-level natural language processing.",
    "In natural language processing, the choice of an appropriate encoding method is crucial to the performance and interpretability of the model, and this principle should not be ignored in the field of protein function prediction as well.",
    "Traditional coding methods, such as one-hot coding and bag-ofwords models, often fail to effectively capture the intrinsic connections between amino acids due to the sparseness of their representations.",
    "In contrast, the adoption of protein language modeling as a coding tool can better capture long-distance dependencies in sequences and provide a deeper understanding of amino acid interactions."
